<p>I taught physics for a year right after undergrad, and I didnâ€™t closely enforce deadlines and late work, because my outlook at that point was, â€œAs long as you do the work, then youâ€™ll learn, so better late than never.â€ And while most of my students did do their work on time, a couple just turned in everything <em>way</em> late. After giving it some thought, I realized those students probably fell into one of two camps:</p>
<ol>
